Linear Regression Project
This repository contains a simple implementation of Linear Regression using Python. The project demonstrates how to build a predictive model using a dataset (score_updated.csv) and evaluate its performance.

Dataset:
The dataset used in this project is:(score_updated.csv)
It typically contains data related to input features (e.g., study hours) and output labels (e.g., scores).

Objective:
The goal of this project is to:
    Understand how Linear Regression works
    Train a model using real data
    Predict output values based on input features
    Evaluate model performance

Technologies Used:
Python 
NumPy
Pandas
Matplotlib
Scikit-learn

Project Workflow:
1.Import required libraries
2.Load the dataset
3.Perform data preprocessing
4.Split dataset into training and testing sets
5.Train the Linear Regression model
6.Make predictions
7.Evaluate the model
8.Visualize results
  
Results:
The model was successfully trained using Linear Regression
Achieved an R² score of 0.97 (97%) on test data
Indicates a strong relationship between study hours and scores

                           Model Performance
Algorithm: Linear Regression
Evaluation Metric: R² Score
Score: 0.97

👉 This means the model explains 97% of the variance in the target variable.
